{
  "style": "IEEE",
  "texts": [
    "Unlike OMG-LLaVA, LLaVA does not produce segmentation masks; instead, it processes image-text pairs to generate natural-language responses without a dedicated segmentation head.",
    "This makes it well-suited for recognition-oriented tasks such as phase, step, action, and count prediction.",
    "Similar to OMG-LLaVA, we follow the two-stage training paradigm of pre-training for general image-text alignment and instruction tuning for task adaptation.",
    "We initialize our models from the official LLaVA checkpoint and perform instruction tuning.",
    "Both experiments are conducted with a batch size of 16, one training epoch, and LoRA [9] for LLM fine-tuning."
  ],
  "correct_citations": [
    "Both experiments are conducted with a batch size of 16, one training epoch, and LoRA [9] for LLM fine-tuning."
  ]
}